# comm-compute-study
Looking at communication vs compute tradeoffs in distributed training

## Project layout

The repository is now set up as an installable Python package using a `src/`
layout:

```text
src/comm_compute_study/
  __init__.py
  __main__.py
  cli.py
  models/
  training/
```

That gives you a main module you can build on for models and training code:

```python
from comm_compute_study.models import ModelSpec
from comm_compute_study.training import TrainingConfig, run_training_loop
```

## Running the package

You can run the module directly:

```bash
python -m comm_compute_study
```

Or through the root wrapper:

```bash
python main.py
```

## Next steps

Put model code in `src/comm_compute_study/models/` and training code in
`src/comm_compute_study/training/`. The starter training loop is intentionally
small so you can swap in your own PyTorch training step logic later.
